SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1055
By Haile
A RESOLUTION to honor Rita Taylor for her top-five finish in
WKRN's Remarkable Women campaign.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in paying tribute
to a lady who has eschewed the materialistic attitude so prevalent in our society to help those
most in need; and
WHEREAS, Rita Taylor of Portland is indeed a "Remarkable Woman" who is always
ready to embark upon a new adventure, usually with her husband, John; and
WHEREAS, a few days after her thirtieth birthday, Mrs. Taylor was forced to face her
own mortality when she was diagnosed with non-Hodgkin lymphoma; and
WHEREAS, since surviving that ordeal, she has lived a happy and purposeful life and
committed herself to paying it forward through countless deeds in service to her fellow human
beings; and
WHEREAS, Rita Taylor has traveled the world on mission trips to the Amazon in Brazil,
Honduras, and Kenya, helping fit glasses and giving the gift of sight; and
WHEREAS, she also conducted a prison ministry for women, hosting Bible study, talent
shows, and arts and crafts, through which she helped many women find a new start in life; and
WHEREAS, for nearly thirty years, Mrs. Taylor hosted and performed in puppet shows in
Portland schools to teach students about the dangers of drugs and alcohol; and
WHEREAS, for the past eight years, her Taylor's Stayin' Alive Divas have put on a
rousing show in Portland to raise money for the American Cancer Society and remind people to
stay on top of their health; and
WHEREAS, Rita and John Taylor volunteer weekly at Hands of Hope Food Pantry and
make deliveries on Saturdays to seniors who are homebound; and
SJR1055
017181
- 1 -

WHEREAS, in addition to the undying gratitude of the many people she has helped, Rita
Taylor has twice been named Citizen of the Year by the Portland Chamber of Commerce, a
most befitting honor that reflects the high regard in which she is held by her community; and
WHEREAS, this devoted wife, mother, friend, neighbor, and self-proclaimed Kansas
farm girl has touched the lives of many through her positive outlook and her devotion to helping
others, and she is most deserving of our approbation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Rita Taylor for her top-five finish in
WKRN's Remarkable Women campaign, commend her bountiful public service, and extend to
her our best wishes for much continued success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
